+# Product/Figma Gate - File Explorer
+
+Status: `PARTIAL`
+Date: 2026-06-09
+Target repo: `trugurpala/pala-os-v5`
+Target feature: file explorer UI for v5
+
+## Court Decision
+
+The file explorer is accepted as the next product-gate candidate, not as an approved implementation import.
+
+Decision: `IMPORT_LATER`
+
+This decision makes the roadmap item actionable by naming the evidence required before v0.dev, shadcn/ui, or old source output can enter v5.
+
+## Scope
+
+The first file explorer pass may include:
+
+- desktop window shell entry
+- navigation tree
+- file list
+- breadcrumbs
+- search
+- empty and loading states
+- selection state
+- settings/form entry point
+- responsive layout proof
+
+The first pass must not include:
+
+- real filesystem mutation
+- external service writes
+- secret access
+- runtime DB import
+- old source bulk copy
+- release, deploy, tag, or public readiness claim
+
+## Source Candidates
+
+| Source | Current decision | Use |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| v0.dev prompt/output | `IMPORT_LATER` | Generate a fresh shadcn/ui-compatible UI shell after this gate records the prompt/output. |
+| Figma design frame | `IMPORT_LATER` | Required design evidence if the feature changes v5 product UI. |
+| `pala-os-v3` and `pala-os-v4` | `REFERENCE` | Patterns for dashboard truth and local control boundaries only. |
+| `pala-os` product/site code | `QUARANTINE` | No direct import; product/admin/site code needs a separate court. |
+
+## Required Proof Before Code
+
+| Requirement | Evidence |
+| --- | --- |
+| Product scope | A short spec naming the file explorer views, states, and non-goals. |
+| Design source | Figma frame URL or v0.dev prompt/output reference. |
+| Data boundary | Explicit choice between mock data, local read-only data, or approved local read-write behavior. |
+| SourceRef | Exact source path or generated output reference for every imported file. |
+| Validation | UI render evidence, responsive evidence, and command output for the repo checks that apply. |
+| Rollback | Normal git revert removes the feature without deleting runtime data. |
+
+## Current Result
+
+Status remains `PARTIAL`.
+
+The feature is now a named migration-court candidate. Implementation remains blocked until the evidence above exists.
